# Build the Observer Dispatcher

## Question

Per the closed redis-channel-fate decision: a dedicated pane in the observer
herdr session running a classifier agent — gpt-5.6-terra at LOW effort,
system-prompt tuned for classify-and-route only (extension-gated identity,
same pattern as the observer: headless, tiny toolset — classify, wake via
herdr agent send, notify via joelclaw notify, drop). Consumes the slimmed
Redis pub/sub (TTLd, emission-budgeted). Allowlist config (VIP, invokes,
anomalies) as data, not code. Woken sessions get reason + pointer, never
payload. Receipts: a VIP-class test signal waking a target pane in under
60s; a non-allowlisted signal correctly dropping to batch.

## Addendum (Joel, 2026-07-13): family awareness + intercom

The dispatcher is a family member, not a lone pane: its context includes
parent (orchestrator) and sibling roles/pane ids, and it reports routing
decisions to the orchestrator via pi-intercom (structured message: signal,
classification, action taken) — so wakes/pages/drops land in the
orchestrator's context and thus in tick reports and memory. Map the actual
intercom API from pi-subagents source (~/.pi/agent/npm/node_modules/pi-subagents/src,
subagent-control.ts + prompt-runtime) — the reply/notification channels are
already live in production workers.
